#Text=Santa Clarita Valley
#Text=Santa Clarita Valley in Southern California is a region of Los Angeles County far to the north of Los Angeles proper .
#Text=Cities
#Text=Agua Dulce
#Text=- A suburban community at the northern end of the valley , home to recreational Castaic Lake .
#Text=-
#Text=The primary city of the valley , home to most of its dining and lodging options as well as the shopping of the upscale Valencia Town Center mall .
#Text=Stevenson Ranch
#Text=- A district of Santa Clarita home to Six Flags Magic Mountain , orange groves , and the CalArts university .
#Text=Other destinations
#Text=- By far the most well-known attraction in the Santa Clarita Valley , famed for its numerous roller coasters which are among the tallest and fastest in the world .

#Text=Vasquez Rocks - A unique rock formation outside Agua Dulce where many movies and television shows have been filmed , including The Flintstones , 24 , and several episodes of the original Star Trek television series .
#Text=Understand
#Text=The Santa Clarita Valley rests between the Golden State Freeway ( Interstate 5 ) and the Antelope Valley Freeway ( State Hwy 14 ) , with new growth swelling beyond these borders .

#Text=The valley is home to a lot of recent suburban development amidst some fairly rural landscape , enough so that the valley 's farmland and surrounding hills have frequently stood in for rural and Old West locations in Hollywood films .
#Text=The hills above the valley are wild enough to be home to bears , mountain lions , coyotes and other wild animals .
#Text=The Pacific Crest Trail runs right through the Santa Clarita Valley .
#Text=Get in
#Text=The closest major airport is located in Burbank , south of the Santa Clarita Valley in the San Fernando Valley , with the more distant LAX serving as a major international hub .

#Text=Interstate 5 is the primary route in and out , traversing the length of the valley from Los Angeles and the San Fernando Valley to the south and continuing north through The Grapevine and on into the San Joaquin Valley .
#Text=CA-14 , the Antelope Valley Freeway , traverses the Soledad Pass between Santa Clarita and the Antelope Valley to the east .

#Text=The Metrolink Antelope Valley Line passes through the Santa Clarita Valley on its way to the Antelope Valley , making three stops in Santa Clarita ( Newhall , Santa Clarita , and Via Princessa ) and offering a direct rail connection to Burbank , Glendale , and Union Station in Downtown Los Angeles .
#Text=The service is geared towards weekday commuters , although there is some evening and weekend service .
#Text=Get around
#Text=Driving is the primary means of getting around , seeing as this is a very suburban and rural region .

#Text=Santa Clarita Transit offers a limited degree of public transit around the developed portion of the valley , with several routes spurring out of the McBean Regional Transit Center at Valencia Blvd and McBean Parkway , across from the Valencia Town Center .
#Text=Routes 5/6 and 4/14 link the transit center to the Newhall Metrolink station , while Routes 3/7 link the transit center to Six Flags Magic Mountain .
#Text=Go next

#Text=The San Fernando Valley lies to the south and is famed as the home of many of the largest Hollywood film studios , including Disney , Warner Brothers , and Universal with its associated Universal Studios theme park .
#Text=The arid landscape of the Antelope Valley lies to the northeast on the other side of the mountains , via CA-14 .
